Sentencas: SrCo0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (SCF), as a promising cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells, possesses a high catalytic activity for the reduction of O-2 to 2O(2-).
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The SCF powder was successfully synthesized by the solid state reaction method and Pechini method and characterized using XRD, particle analysis, and electrochemical performance measurements.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: Smaller-particle-size SCF materials (SCF-P) with single phase are obtained at lower synthesis temperature by the Pechini method and possess better electrochemical performance as compared with those prepared by the solid state reaction method.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The reason is that the Pechini method involves the mixing of elements at atomic level, so pure SCF phase formation can be accelerated and showed high electrocatalytic activity.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The preparation procedure of SCF cathode was firstly investigated using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: Results show that the total polarization resistance and the low-frequency resistance decrease gradually with the reduction of the calcination temperature for the SCF cathodes.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The SCF-P cathode sintered at 1,000 A degrees C possesses the highest porosity and the best electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: It is the result of a comprehensive function of three-phase boundary length, porosity of cathode, and the adhesion between cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The charge-transfer process, together with the adsorption, dissociation, and diffusion of oxygen, has a strong influence on the whole reaction process of the cathode.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite

Sentencas: The influence of binder amounts on the performance of the SCF-P cathodes was also studied.
Titulo: Influences of synthesis route and preparation process on the electrochemical properties of Fe-doped strontium cobaltite
